+---
+name: task-review
+description: Evidence-based review of Formic tasks in the Review column. Verifies the work actually landed against acceptance criteria and issues APPROVE or RE-RUN verdicts. Supports batch mode for clearing review backlogs.
+---
+
+# Task Review — Evidence-Based Review Column Triage
+
+Review is Formic's chronic bottleneck: a previous epoch ended with 67 of 68 tasks stuck
+in Review. This skill produces a decisive, evidence-backed verdict per task so the human
+only has to confirm, not investigate.
+
+**Usage:** review a single task (`/task-review t-2`) or the whole column (`/task-review batch`).
+
+## Per-task procedure
+
+### 1. Load the task's own artifacts — beware stale data
+- Task docs: `.formic/tasks/<id>_<slug>/` — read `README.md` (acceptance criteria),
+  `PLAN.md`, `declared-files.json`, and `QUALITY.md` if present.
+- **ID-collision warning:** board resets restart numbering, so multiple directories can
+  share one bare id (e.g. two `t-3_*` dirs). Match on the **slug**, not just the id.
+- Logs: prefer the merged `.formic/logs/<id>/task.log`; per-step files (`execute.log`
+  etc.) may be stale leftovers from an earlier epoch — check that paths mentioned inside
+  the log match this task's slug before trusting it.
+
+### 2. Locate the actual changes
+```bash
+git log --oneline --all | grep -i "<task-id>"        # auto-save: before task <id>
+git diff <commit-before>..<commit-after> --stat
+```
+The window between "auto-save: before task t-N" and the next task's auto-save commit
+approximates t-N's changes. Inspect the diff itself, not just the stat.
+
+### 3. Verify against acceptance criteria
+For each criterion in the task context / README.md, record PASS/FAIL with evidence
+(file:line in the diff, test output, or a command you ran). Additionally check:
+- Diff is non-empty for a code task (history includes "complete" claims with +0 −0)
+- `npx tsc --noEmit` passes on the current tree
+- No forbidden practices introduced (`any`, `require()`, missing `.js` extensions,
+  `console.log`, sync fs, empty catch)
+- For non-code tasks (docs, Confluence, config): open the produced artifact and confirm
+  it exists and matches the request — do not trust the agent summary.
+
+### 4. Verdict
+
+- **APPROVE** — all criteria PASS. State this plainly with the evidence table.
+- **RE-RUN** — one or more criteria FAIL. Draft the exact re-run context: quote the
+  failing criteria, the evidence of failure, and (if diagnosable) the suspected cause,
+  so the re-run doesn't repeat the mistake. If it's a defect rather than incomplete
+  work, recommend a new fix task using the root-cause-fix protocol instead of a re-run.
+
+You are read-only: report verdicts to the user; they click Approve/Re-run on the board.
+
+## Batch mode
+
+1. List every task in the Review column from the board state.
+2. Run the per-task procedure on each (oldest first).
+3. Output a summary table first, details after:
+
+| Task | Title | Verdict | Blocking issue (if RE-RUN) |
+|------|-------|---------|----------------------------|
+| t-1  | Merge per-step logs | APPROVE | — |
+| t-2  | ... | RE-RUN | criterion 3 failed: no regression test |
+
+4. End with the one-line action list for the human ("Approve t-1, t-3; re-run t-2 with
+   the context below").
