+---
+name: quality-gate
+description: End-of-execution verification gate for Formic tasks. Proves the work landed with real evidence (diff, build, tests, forbidden-practice scan) and writes QUALITY.md. Run before reporting any task complete.
+---
+
+# Quality Gate — Evidence-Based Completion Check
+
+**Task Title:** $TASK_TITLE
+**Task Documentation:** $TASK_DOCS_PATH
+
+You are the final gate before this task is reported complete. Task history shows agents
+reporting "all subtasks completed" with **+0 −0 code changes**, and 7 separate follow-up
+"verify" tasks created because execution ended with claims instead of evidence. Your job
+is to make completion claims impossible without proof.
+
+## Rules
+
+- **Never fabricate a pass.** If a check fails, report the failure verbatim and either fix
+  it or mark the task incomplete. A truthful failure is a success of this gate.
+- Every check below must be backed by actual command output, not a summary of what you
+  expect the output to be.
+
+## Checks
+
+### 1. The diff is real and scoped
+```bash
+git diff --stat HEAD
+git status --porcelain
+```
+- FAIL if the combined diff is empty for a task that requires code changes.
+- FAIL if files were modified that are neither in `$TASK_DOCS_PATH/declared-files.json`
+  (exclusive list) nor obviously required (explain any exceptions).
+
+### 2. Types and build
+```bash
+npx tsc --noEmit
+```
+- Must exit 0. If the task touched build config or entry points, also run `npm run build`.
+
+### 3. Tests
+- If the server API changed: `python test/run_tests.py` (requires the dev server running —
+  start it with `npm run dev` in the background if needed).
+- If UI behavior changed: `npx playwright test` (or the relevant spec only).
+- If a test suite cannot be run in this environment, say so explicitly — do not imply it passed.
+
+### 4. Forbidden-practice scan (on the diff only)
+```bash
+git diff HEAD -U0 | grep -nE '^\+' | grep -vE '^\+\+\+' | grep -nE \
+  '(: any\b|<any>|as any|require\(|console\.log\(|readFileSync|writeFileSync|existsSync)'
+```
+Also manually verify in the diff:
+- Relative imports include the `.js` extension
+- No empty `catch {}` blocks; every catch logs with a `[ServiceName]` prefix or re-throws
+- No `TODO:`/`FIXME:` comments were deleted
+- No new dependencies added to package.json
+
+### 5. Acceptance criteria
+Read the acceptance criteria from `$TASK_DOCS_PATH/README.md` (or the task context).
+For each criterion, record PASS/FAIL with one line of evidence (command output,
+file:line reference, or test name).
+
+## Output — write QUALITY.md
+
+Write the results to `$TASK_DOCS_PATH/QUALITY.md`:
+
+```markdown
+# Quality Gate — <task title>
+Date: <date>   Verdict: PASS | FAIL
+
+| # | Check | Result | Evidence |
+|---|-------|--------|----------|
+| 1 | Diff non-empty & scoped | PASS | 3 files, +42 −7, matches declared-files |
+| 2 | tsc --noEmit | PASS | exit 0 |
+| 3 | Tests | PASS | run_tests.py: 24 passed |
+| 4 | Forbidden practices | PASS | scan clean |
+| 5 | Acceptance criteria | PASS | 4/4 (see below) |
+
+## Acceptance criteria detail
+1. <criterion> — PASS — <evidence>
+...
+
+## Notes / deviations
+<anything the reviewer should know>
+```
+
+Then include the verdict table in your handoff summary. If the verdict is FAIL,
+the handoff must open with `QUALITY GATE FAILED:` and the failing checks.
