+---
+name: board-hygiene
+description: Audit .formic/ state health — task-ID collisions across board epochs, stale logs, corrupted board.json files, duplicate open tasks, and review-column aging. Run periodically or after a board reset.
+---
+
+# Board Hygiene — .formic State Audit
+
+Formic's board can be reset, which restarts task numbering at t-1 while `.formic/tasks/`
+and `.formic/logs/` keep old directories keyed by the same bare `t-N`. Observed damage:
+`logs/t-2/execute.log` containing output from an unrelated earlier t-2, duplicate dirs
+for t-3/t-72/t-75/t-bootstrap, and 7 `board.json.corrupted.*` files. This skill detects
+and reports that rot. You are read-only — output findings and a cleanup task, do not delete.
+
+## Audit steps
+
+### 1. Live board vs. task directories (ID collisions)
+```bash
+python3 - <<'EOF'
+import json, os, re, collections
+board = json.load(open('.formic/board.json'))
+tasks = board['tasks']
+live = {t['id']: t for t in (tasks.values() if isinstance(tasks, dict) else tasks)}
+dirs = collections.defaultdict(list)
+for d in os.listdir('.formic/tasks'):
+    m = re.match(r'(t-[\w]+)_(.*)', d)
+    if m: dirs[m.group(1)].append(d)
+print("== IDs with multiple task dirs (epoch collisions) ==")
+for tid, ds in sorted(dirs.items()):
+    if len(ds) > 1: print(tid, '->', ds)
+print("\n== Live tasks and their matching dir ==")
+for tid, t in live.items():
+    matches = dirs.get(tid, [])
+    print(tid, t.get('status'), '| dirs:', matches or 'MISSING')
+print("\n== Orphaned dirs (no live task) ==")
+orphans = [d for tid, ds in dirs.items() if tid not in live for d in ds]
+print(len(orphans), 'orphaned task dirs')
+EOF
+```
+
+### 2. Stale / cross-contaminated logs
+For each live task id, check `.formic/logs/<id>/`:
+- Per-step files (`brief.log`, `plan.log`, `execute.log`) that reference a **different
+  slug** than the live task's docsPath are stale leftovers — flag them.
+- The merged `task.log` is authoritative for runs after the log-merge feature (t-1).
+- Log dirs with no live task are orphans.
+
+### 3. Corrupted and backup board files
+```bash
+ls -la .formic/board.json* 
+```
+Flag every `board.json.corrupted.*` and stale `board.json.backup`. Multiple corruption
+files indicate a persistence bug — if new ones appear after the last known fix, recommend
+a `root-cause-fix` task, not just cleanup.
+
+### 4. Duplicate / near-duplicate open tasks
+Compare titles of all Todo/Queued/Review tasks pairwise (normalized keywords). The
+plugin epoch produced three near-identical decomposition waves (t-28–33 / t-34–40 /
+t-41–47) — catching this early saves the most agent time of any check here.
+
+### 5. Review-column aging
+For each Review task, report how long it has sat there (task `updatedAt` vs today) and
+whether it has a `QUALITY.md`. If more than ~5 tasks are in Review, recommend running
+`/task-review batch`.
+
+### 6. Tools registry
+```bash
+ls .formic/tools | wc -l
+```
+Check for duplicated commands across tool entries (same command registered under
+multiple names) and report counts.
+
+## Output
+
+1. A findings report ordered by severity: data-loss risks (corruption) → active
+   contamination (ID collisions on live tasks) → waste (duplicates) → clutter (orphans).
+2. A ready-to-create Formic cleanup task (via task-craft) whose context lists the exact
+   move/archive commands, e.g.:
+   ```bash
+   mkdir -p .formic/archive/<today>
+   mv .formic/tasks/<orphan-dir> .formic/logs/<orphan-id> .formic/board.json.corrupted.* .formic/archive/<today>/
+   ```
+   Archive, never delete — old docs are the only record of past epochs.
+3. If ID collisions on **live** tasks were found, recommend a `standard` task to make
+   Formic key task/log directories by epoch or full slug instead of bare `t-N`.
