+---
+name: root-cause-fix
+description: Disciplined bug-fix protocol for Formic fix tasks — reproduce, root-cause, sibling scan, regression test. Use for any task whose title starts with Fix or that addresses a defect.
+---
+
+# Root-Cause Fix — Bug Fix Protocol
+
+**Task Title:** $TASK_TITLE
+**Task Context:** $TASK_CONTEXT
+**Task Documentation:** $TASK_DOCS_PATH
+
+This project's history shows the cost of symptom-patching: the "declare step re-running
+on resume" bug took **three consecutive tasks** (t-71, t-72, t-73) to actually fix, with
+follow-on defects (t-74, t-78) leaking from the same area. Follow this protocol so one
+fix task means one fixed bug.
+
+## Phase 1 — Reproduce (before touching any code)
+
+1. Restate the observed symptom from the task context in one sentence.
+2. Reproduce it: run the failing command, hit the API route, or write a minimal script
+   that demonstrates the wrong behavior. Capture the output.
+3. If you cannot reproduce it, STOP and investigate why — check logs in
+   `.formic/logs/<task-id>/task.log`, git history of the affected file
+   (`git log -p --follow -- <file>`), and recent auto-save commits.
+   Do not "fix" what you cannot observe; report findings instead.
+
+## Phase 2 — Root cause
+
+4. Trace the mechanism from symptom to cause. Write it as a causal chain:
+   *"X happens because function A does B, which leaves state C, so when D runs it E."*
+5. Distinguish the **defect** (wrong code) from the **trigger** (conditions exposing it).
+   The fix must remove the defect, not just avoid the trigger.
+6. Ask: could this defect corrupt persisted state (`.formic/board.json`, `leases.json`,
+   task docs)? If yes, also check whether existing state is already corrupted and needs
+   repair or migration.
+
+## Phase 3 — Sibling scan
+
+7. Search the codebase for the same defect pattern elsewhere:
+   ```bash
+   grep -rn "<pattern that characterizes the defect>" src/
+   ```
+   Example: if the bug was a missing existence check before re-running a step, check every
+   other workflow step for the same missing check. Fix in-scope siblings; list
+   out-of-scope ones in the handoff so they become their own task.
+
+## Phase 4 — Fix + regression test
+
+8. Implement the minimal fix that removes the defect. No drive-by refactors.
+9. Add a regression test that **fails without the fix and passes with it**:
+   - API-level behavior → add a test in `test/` (Python unittest + requests)
+   - UI behavior → add/extend a Playwright spec in `e2e/`
+   - If neither harness can express it, write a reproduction script and include its
+     before/after output in the handoff.
+10. Re-run the reproduction from Phase 1 and show it now behaves correctly.
+
+## Phase 5 — Verify and hand off
+
+11. Run the full quality-gate checklist (diff scoped, `npx tsc --noEmit`, tests,
+    forbidden-practice scan) and write `$TASK_DOCS_PATH/QUALITY.md`.
+12. The handoff summary MUST contain:
+    - **Root cause:** the causal chain from step 4
+    - **Fix:** files:lines changed and why this removes the defect
+    - **Regression test:** name/location and proof it fails without the fix
+    - **Siblings:** other occurrences found and their disposition
